chat_history.content:
Great question! Ryan Fitzpatrick was the starting quarterback for the New York Jets in 2015. He played a total of 16 games that year for the team.

Ryan Fitzpatrick has had quite the career, playing for several teams throughout his time in the NFL. He played for the St. Louis Rams from 2005 to 2006, the Cincinnati Bengals from 2007 to 2008, and then the Buffalo Bills from 2009 to 2012. He also had a stint with the Tennessee Titans from 2013 to 2014 before joining the New York Jets in 2015. After the Jets, he played for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers in 2016 and 2017, and then the Miami Dolphins from 2019 to 2020. 

As for the head coaches of these teams during his time there, it varies:
- St. Louis Rams: Mike Martz (2005), Scott Linehan (2006)
- Cincinnati Bengals: Marvin Lewis
- Buffalo Bills: Dick Jauron (2009-2010), Chan Gailey (2010-2012)
- Tennessee Titans: Mike Mularkey (2013-2014)
- New York Jets: Todd Bowles (2015-2018)
- Tampa Bay Buccaneers: Dirk Koetter (2016), Dirk Koetter and Mike Smith (2017)
- Miami Dolphins: Brian Flores (2019-2020), and then Brian Flores and Pat Fitzgerald (2020).

Do you want to know more about Ryan Fitzpatrick's career or any of these teams and their head coaches?
